Aqua Europa eight years ago established the Brussels Water Alliance, an informal network of trade bodies with interests in the water sector.&#xd;
&#xd;
In 2016 formed a group of some 30 Brussels-based trade bodies representing industries involved with the supply of products or materials used in drinking water applications that are connected to municipal drinking water supplies within the European Union.  to address the current lack of harmonisation of regulatory requirements within the EU covering products and materials used in applications involving contact with drinking water. The objective is to achieve a single scheme for assessment and certification of products and materials that are used in drinking water applications, which will be accepted in all EU Member States.&#xd;
&#xd;
Member of the Europan Water Alliance and WssTP
